com.vernalis.pdbconnector2.dialogcomponents

Interface SettingsModelRangeBounded<T>

  • Type Parameters:
    T - The type of the value stored. If T implements Comparable, then the related SettingsModelComparableRangeBounded interface should be used
    All Known Subinterfaces:
    SettingsModelComparableRangeBounded<T>
    All Known Implementing Classes:
    AbstractSettingsModelRangeBounded, SettingsModelDateRangeBounded, SettingsModelDoubleRangeBounded, SettingsModelIntegerRangeBounded

    public interface SettingsModelRangeBounded<T>
    An interface defining the methods needed for a settings model defining a bounded range - ie a range with limits on the possible upper and lower values. Implementations should typically extend SettingsModel.
    Since:
    1.28.0
    Author:
    S.Roughley knime@vernalis.com
    See Also:
    SettingsModelComparableRangeBounded, AbstractSettingsModelRangeBounded

      • validateRange

        default void validateRange(T lowerVal,
                           T upperVal)
        Method to validate the range supplied. The values should be in the order lower bound <= lower value <(=*) upper value <= upper bound. *Equal values may be allowed according to the result of allowEqualUpperLower(). The default implementation validates each value and then the actual range
        Parameters:
        lowerVal - The lower value of the range
        upperVal - The upper value of the range
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the range is not valid
        See Also:
        validateValue(Object)

      • validateValue

        default void validateValue(T val)
        Method to validate a value. In this case, the check is whether the value is within the specified bounds as it is unknown whether this is an upper or lower value
        Parameters:
        val - The value to check
        Throws:
        java.lang.IllegalArgumentException - if the value is outside the allowed bounds
        See Also:
        validateRange(Object, Object)

      • compareValues

        int compareValues(T t0,
                  T t1)
        Method to compare a pair of values. Should return a value <0 when t0 < t1, 0 then t0 and t1 are equal and >0 when t0 > t1
        Parameters:
        t0 - The first value to compare
        t1 - The second value to compare
        Returns:
        The result of the comparison as described above
